Core Principle

Reality is rarely observed by one perfect witness.

Instead, it is sampled by countless imperfect observers.

The Reality Reconstruction Engine treats every observation as a probabilistic brushstroke on a shared canvas.

Its purpose is not to invent reality, but to reconstruct the highest-confidence model that explains the available evidence while explicitly representing uncertainty.

